I will not invite a wizard into an xp group without an enchanter or bard.  When I am playing my cleric (40) and I do not have my pet enchanter available, that wiz  can go quad. sorry, but wizards make for slower kills, with the low damage and lack of agro management.  (agro  management is a whole 'nother thread...) My bard will always invite a wizard, (mana is not in such short supply then)<br>
<br>
It is the casual player that is hurt by the lack of  group viability in the lower levels.  Usually the casual player is playing for social reasons.  He or she obviously doesnt mind fast xp, but that is not the primary  purpose of play.  As a result, casual  players (at least me) want to group and we want to be effective members of the group.  <br>
<br>
I hope this doesnt sound like too much disjointed ramblings. Basically I want the original  document submitted because I agree 100 percent.<br>
